lvl 28 Ogre ShadowKnightFheng lvl 41 Iksar Monk</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uobiquon1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Obiquon1</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/27/02 5:52:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14738.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wizard seeks advice about legends</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> All of the content is designed primarily for the high level crowd<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br>I would have to disagee. I'd say 7 of 10 GM events are based for those under level 50. However, I do agree that MM is a raiding zone for those 50+. Other than that (and oasis's new content) the content of SH is really no different than any other server.<br><br>I've talked to a few ppl leaving that have said &quot;SH blows, its the same a server_01&quot;.  well ok, thats fair but what did you expect? if youre camping/killing and not do anything different well yeah, you're right $40 would be a waste. But for me going to the GM events is the fun I wanted. running thru BB and seeing the goblin raiding parties attack Kaladim, seeing Orc march against Kethelin, seeing DE's attacking the merchants in EC, pvp events and the list goes on.<br><br>Stormhammer is what you make it. If you come to get loot that &quot;drops like candy&quot; you will be dissapointed. If you think things are easier on SH you will be dissapointed. If you think everyzone has been made over with new loot and adventure you will be dissapointed.<br><br>Again, everyone has come for different reasons. the server is still &quot;in flux&quot; trying to find itself (I expect this to last a few more months).<br><br>I hope both views give you more insight and IF you move over, send me a tell and we can get a AE group going. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ukaziqueal.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kaziqueal</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/27/02 6:38:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14738.topic&index=27>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wizard seeks advice about legends</span><hr size=1> The Zek people are annoying, for some reason they seem to feel the need to share their server politics with everyone. From what I hear though, many will be gone back to zek after they are done &quot;gearing up&quot;.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrishnaka.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grishnaka</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/27/02 6:55:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14738.topic&index=28>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wizard seeks advice about legends</span><hr size=1> Well...<br><br>Obiquon...I have to disagree with you to a certain extent...The server is only what you make of it if you are over 50.  If you come looking for low level content, its just not really there unless youa re participating in one of the create a new character events.<br><br>My Shaman is Lvl 50, and is almost 3 years old.  I brought him over originally with my baby wiz to check things out.  I made the mistake of joining a guild at random (yes I should have known better) in the first couple of days during the guilding frenzy.  I have never in my entire EQ carreer met SOOO many self centered loot whores in my entire life.  I swear 15 minutes of guild chat I saw the word loot more times that I care to imagine.<br><br>Maybe I got unlucky...<br><br>Maybe I found the bad seeds...<br><br>I disbanded. <br><br>So now im on a server where I cant really play either of my characters unless I feel like soloing...its kind of depressing...<br><br>I have been to a couple of event, some of the were fun. some of them, not so much.  Over all  I think its just improtant to note that there arent a lot of pickup groups around.  If you move over, you will need to find a guild or a group of friends...with out them, your options are severly limited<br><br>Grishnaka <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uobiquon1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Obiquon1</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/27/02 7:45:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14738.topic&index=29>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wizard seeks advice about legends</span><hr size=1> Grishnaka,<br><br>hehe, I think you are going thru the pain of adapting to a server with a small population (even above 50). getting a pick-up group is always tough. however, my son plays a 15 pally and 11 druid (druid is guilded) and is having a blast.<br><br>Its pretty obvious I'm pro-legends but I've had nothing but mostly positive exeriences.  Everyone is different and if SH is not for you thats cool too.<br><br>remember, everything is what you make it to be. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uphaedran.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Phaedran</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/27/02 10:00:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14738.topic&index=30>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wizard seeks advice about legends</span><hr size=1> I play on Legends and am having the the best time in EQ I've had in a good long while! The GM's really make the grade for this server; They show up and actually take an interest in what's going on! Case in point: After my guild took out Dain (we were being watched byGM's) a cleric was awarded the belt. Well, everyone got ready to leave when all of a sudden GM controlled Coldain started spawning, shouting &quot;Stop him he has the Dains Belt!&quot; next thing you know all hell broke loose and there was a 10th ring like war going on in Icewell keep. <br>Another event: I was minding my own business in Sebilis one night when all of a sudden a froglock named Tamichi 'Ku ( it was something liek that)  spawns and some GM Human paladin.  He starts going on about the Evil within Sebilis that must be vanquished. Well, this ended up being a GM lead Trakanon raid! He was an active member lol. So we get down to Trak and waste him. Then the Froglock Tamichi spawns again and starts going on about Stew or some such. So the raid ends and I go back to Xping....every frog in Sebilis has as part of it's loot table Lion meat stew! Also, some lame ass rogue at the end of the fight decided to attack Tamichi to which the froglok started screaming &quot;GUARDS! GUARDS!&quot; and then a bunch of myconoids spawned and killed his aggressors. So after all the fighting and TL's I stayed in Traks lair by myself for a few minutes and Tamichi reappeared and we had a lovely discussion about the relation of the Frogloks of Guk to those of Sebilis among other things heh.   I know for you loot ho's that sounds sort of stupid, but for me it was novel and made me smile....that's the phatest lewts around.  I had fun, isn't that the point of this game? <br>Phaedran Dimensionale <br>Socerer of Enrapture - Stormhammer <br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umelegaunt.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Melegaunt</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/27/02 11:00:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14738.topic&index=31>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.public.iastate.edu/~eckerman/KOTG/pics/familiarface.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wizard seeks advice about legends</span><hr size=1> So all in all it sounds cool if you are willing to pay the money. <p><p><CENTER><IMG SRC="http://personal.msy.bellsouth.net/~dentont/eqpics/Melegaunt.gif"><BR><A HREF="http://www.geocities.com/arcasylum">Arcane Asylum</A> |<A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=39165">Profile</A> | <a href="http://www.drinal.com">Drinal</A><BR> </CENTER></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwhizbangdustyboots.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Whizbang Dustyboots</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer<BR>Gnomish Advocate</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/27/02 11:45:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14738.topic&index=21>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.lby3.com/eq/whiz/flappy.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wizard seeks advice about legends</span><hr size=1> I wonder how many people would go to, or stay on Stormhammer, if they had the option of moving their characters to a different server without losing all their gear. I know of a number of people who are there to avoid Zeks or because their home server blows. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uobiquon1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Obiquon1</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/27/02 11:56:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14738.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wizard seeks advice about legends</span><hr size=1> whiz, you keep your gear moving to and from SH.  Or did I missunderstand your statement? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwhizbangdustyboots.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Whizbang Dustyboots</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer<BR>Gnomish Advocate</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/27/02 12:17:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14738.topic&index=32>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.lby3.com/eq/whiz/flappy.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wizard seeks advice about legends</span><hr size=1> Yes. Pretend someone could move from Rallos Zek to Vazaelle without losing gear. How many people would do something like THAT rather than going to Legends?<br><br>i.e. how many people are there for the new server with their current characters, and not for the special content?<br><br>Personally, the special content sounds pretty good (not $40 good, but pretty good) but even moreso the chance to group with people I know from other servers. But I'm not sure $40 a month for that alone would be a good sell for all such folks, you know?<br><br>Just thinking aloud here that maybe VI needs two tiers of paid server moves, with a, say, $100 with all gear move as the upper tier one. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessageRange?topicID=14738.topic&start=21&stop=23>2</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showPrevMessage?topicID=14738.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showNextMessage?topicID=14738.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14738.topic&index=32><img src=http://www.graffe.com/messageboard/add_reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.emailToFriend?topicID=14738.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.threadControl?topicID=14738.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=14738.topi